  exerciseName: EnumsNotStrings
  exerciseTitle: Use Enums not strings
  exerciseText: Refactor this code to work with an Enum type so we can avoid using
    strings as identifiers.
  hintText: Define an enum ObjectType
  solutionText: "public enum ObjectType {\r\n    Player,\r\n    Enemy,\r\n    Barrel\r\n}\n\r\npublic
    void HandleObject(ObjectType objectType) {\r\n    switch (objectType) {\r\n       
    case ObjectType.Player:\r\n            // Do something with Player\r\n           
    break;\r\n        case ObjectType.Enemy:\r\n            // Do something with
    Enemy\r\n            break;\r\n        case ObjectType.Barrel:\r\n           
    // Do something with Barrel\r\n            break;\r\n    }\r\n}"
  completedText: "Here you learned how to refactor your code to avoid using strings
    as identifiers. \r\nStrings are very brittle and very easy to make mistakes whereas
    with Enums or direct object references, if you make a typing mistake the compiler
    will help you."
